# Wails WebView2 remote debugging for Playwright E2E tests
#
# IMPORTANT: Wails does NOT read .env files automatically.
# You MUST set this env var in your shell BEFORE running `wails dev`:
#
#   PowerShell:
#     $env:WEBVIEW2_ADDITIONAL_BROWSER_ARGUMENTS = '--remote-debugging-port=9222'
#     wails dev
#
#   Or use the helper script:
#     .\MikuMikuAR\start-e2e.ps1
#
# Then run E2E tests (another terminal):
#     cd MikuMikuAR/frontend && npx playwright test
#
# Alternatively, for DOM-only UI tests (no WebView2 needed):
#   Terminal 1: cd MikuMikuAR/frontend && npm run dev
#   Terminal 2: npx playwright test (uses vitePage fixture → localhost:5173)
#
# https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/webview2/how-to/remote-debugging
